 115// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.ExpandBits
 116// Make sure the array supports at least NBITS bits.
 117// This function is the same as AllocBit(NBITS - 1) assuming NBITS > 0;
 118void algo_lib::ary_ExpandBits(algo_lib::Bitset& parent, u32 n_bits) {
 119    u64 n_elems = (n_bits+63) >> 6;
 120    while (true) {
 121        u64 n = ary_N(parent);
 122        if (n_elems <= n) break;
 123        ary_Alloc(parent) = 0; // keep stretching
 124    }
 125}

 127// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.AllocBit
 128// Make sure all bits up to and including #BIT_IDX exist
 129// New values are initialized with zero.
 130void algo_lib::ary_AllocBit(algo_lib::Bitset& parent, u32 bit_idx) {
 131    ary_ExpandBits(parent, bit_idx + 1);
 132}

 134// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.Addary
 135// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
 136// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
 137// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
 138algo::aryptr<u64> algo_lib::ary_Addary(algo_lib::Bitset& parent, algo::aryptr<u64> rhs) {
 139    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= parent.ary_elems && rhs.elems < parent.ary_elems + parent.ary_max;
 140    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
 141        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_alias  field:algo_lib.Bitset.ary  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
 142    }
 143    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
 144    ary_Reserve(parent, nnew); // reserve space
 145    int at = parent.ary_n;
 146    memcpy(parent.ary_elems + at, rhs.elems, nnew * sizeof(u64));
 147    parent.ary_n += nnew;
 148    return algo::aryptr<u64>(parent.ary_elems + at, nnew);
 149}

 151// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.Alloc
 152// Reserve space. Insert element at the end
 153// The new element is initialized to a default value
 154u64& algo_lib::ary_Alloc(algo_lib::Bitset& parent) {
 155    ary_Reserve(parent, 1);
 156    int n  = parent.ary_n;
 157    int at = n;
 158    u64 *elems = parent.ary_elems;
 159    new (elems + at) u64(0); // construct new element, default initializer
 160    parent.ary_n = n+1;
 161    return elems[at];
 162}

 164// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.AllocAt
 165// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
 166// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
 167u64& algo_lib::ary_AllocAt(algo_lib::Bitset& parent, int at) {
 168    ary_Reserve(parent, 1);
 169    int n  = parent.ary_n;
 170    if (UNLIKELY(u64(at) >= u64(n+1))) {
 171        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.bad_alloc_at  field:algo_lib.Bitset.ary  comment:'index out of range'");
 172    }
 173    u64 *elems = parent.ary_elems;
 174    memmove(elems + at + 1, elems + at, (n - at) * sizeof(u64));
 175    new (elems + at) u64(0); // construct element, default initializer
 176    parent.ary_n = n+1;
 177    return elems[at];
 178}

 180// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.AllocN
 181// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
 182algo::aryptr<u64> algo_lib::ary_AllocN(algo_lib::Bitset& parent, int n_elems) {
 183    ary_Reserve(parent, n_elems);
 184    int old_n  = parent.ary_n;
 185    int new_n = old_n + n_elems;
 186    u64 *elems = parent.ary_elems;
 187    for (int i = old_n; i < new_n; i++) {
 188        new (elems + i) u64(0); // construct new element, default initialize
 189    }
 190    parent.ary_n = new_n;
 191    return algo::aryptr<u64>(elems + old_n, n_elems);
 192}

 194// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.Remove
 195// Remove item by index. If index outside of range, do nothing.
 196void algo_lib::ary_Remove(algo_lib::Bitset& parent, u32 i) {
 197    u32 lim = parent.ary_n;
 198    u64 *elems = parent.ary_elems;
 199    if (i < lim) {
 200        memmove(elems + i, elems + (i + 1), sizeof(u64) * (lim - (i + 1)));
 201        parent.ary_n = lim - 1;
 202    }
 203}

 205// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.RemoveLast
 206// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 207void algo_lib::ary_RemoveLast(algo_lib::Bitset& parent) {
 208    u64 n = parent.ary_n;
 209    if (n > 0) {
 210        n -= 1;
 211        parent.ary_n = n;
 212    }
 213}

 215// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.AbsReserve
 216// Make sure N elements fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
 217void algo_lib::ary_AbsReserve(algo_lib::Bitset& parent, int n) {
 218    u32 old_max  = parent.ary_max;
 219    if (n > i32(old_max)) {
 220        u32 new_max  = i32_Max(i32_Max(old_max * 2, n), 4);
 221        void *new_mem = algo_lib::lpool_ReallocMem(parent.ary_elems, old_max * sizeof(u64), new_max * sizeof(u64));
 222        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 223            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_nomem  field:algo_lib.Bitset.ary  comment:'out of memory'");
 224        }
 225        parent.ary_elems = (u64*)new_mem;
 226        parent.ary_max = new_max;
 227    }
 228}

 230// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.Setary
 231// Copy contents of RHS to PARENT.
 232void algo_lib::ary_Setary(algo_lib::Bitset& parent, algo_lib::Bitset &rhs) {
 233    ary_RemoveAll(parent);
 234    int nnew = rhs.ary_n;
 235    ary_Reserve(parent, nnew); // reserve space
 236    for (int i = 0; i < nnew; i++) { // copy elements over
 237        new (parent.ary_elems + i) u64(ary_qFind(rhs, i));
 238        parent.ary_n = i + 1;
 239    }
 240}

 250// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary.AllocNVal
 251// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
 252algo::aryptr<u64> algo_lib::ary_AllocNVal(algo_lib::Bitset& parent, int n_elems, const u64& val) {
 253    ary_Reserve(parent, n_elems);
 254    int old_n  = parent.ary_n;
 255    int new_n = old_n + n_elems;

 278// --- algo_lib.Bitset.ary_bitcurs.Next
 279// proceed to next item
 280void algo_lib::Bitset_ary_bitcurs_Next(Bitset_ary_bitcurs &curs) {
 281    ++curs.bit;
 282    int index = curs.bit / 64;
 283    int offset = curs.bit % 64;
 284    for (; index < curs.n_elems; ++index, offset = 0) {
 285        u64 rest = curs.elems[index] >> offset;
 286        if (rest) {
 287            offset += algo::u64_BitScanForward(rest);
 288            break;
 289        }
 290    }
 291    curs.bit = index * 64 + offset;
 292}

 431        }
 432        case algo_lib_FieldId_d: {
 433            retval = d_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent, strval);
 434            break;
 435        }
 436        case algo_lib_FieldId_sig: {
 437            retval = sig_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent, strval);
 438            break;
 439        }
 440        case algo_lib_FieldId_h: {
 441            retval = h_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent, strval);
 442            break;
 443        }
 444        default: break;
 445    }
 446    if (!retval) {
 447        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 448    }
 449    return retval;
 450}

 452// --- algo_lib.Cmdline..ReadTupleMaybe
 453// Read fields of algo_lib::Cmdline from attributes of ascii tuple TUPLE
 454bool algo_lib::Cmdline_ReadTupleMaybe(algo_lib::Cmdline &parent, algo::Tuple &tuple) {
 455    bool retval = true;
 456    ind_beg(algo::Tuple_attrs_curs,attr,tuple) {
 457        retval = Cmdline_ReadFieldMaybe(parent, attr.name, attr.value);
 458        if (!retval) {
 459            break;
 460        }
 461    }ind_end;
 462    return retval;
 463}

 465// --- algo_lib.Cmdline..NArgs
 466// Used with command lines
 467// Return # of command-line arguments that must follow this argument
 468// If FIELD is invalid, return -1
 469i32 algo_lib::Cmdline_NArgs(algo_lib::FieldId field, algo::strptr& out_dflt, bool* out_anon) {
 470    i32 retval = 1;
 471    switch (field) {
 472        case algo_lib_FieldId_verbose: { // $comment
 473            *out_anon = false;
 474            retval=0;
 475            out_dflt="1";
 476        } break;
 477        case algo_lib_FieldId_debug: { // dmmeta.fflag: emptyval specified; no argument required but value may be specified as verbose:value
 478            *out_anon = false;
 479            retval=0;
 480            out_dflt="1";
 481        } break;
 482        case algo_lib_FieldId_help: { // dmmeta.fflag: emptyval specified; no argument required but value may be specified as debug:value
 483            *out_anon = false;
 484            retval=0;
 485            out_dflt="Y";
 486        } break;
 487        case algo_lib_FieldId_version: { // bool: no argument required but value may be specified as help:Y
 488            *out_anon = false;
 489            retval=0;
 490            out_dflt="Y";
 491        } break;
 492        case algo_lib_FieldId_signature: { // bool: no argument required but value may be specified as version:Y
 493            *out_anon = false;
 494            retval=0;
 495            out_dflt="Y";
 496        } break;
 497        case algo_lib_FieldId_v: { // bool: no argument required but value may be specified as signature:Y
 498            *out_anon = false;
 499            retval=0;
 500            out_dflt="1";
 501        } break;
 502        case algo_lib_FieldId_d: { // dmmeta.fflag: emptyval specified; no argument required but value may be specified as v:value
 503            *out_anon = false;
 504            retval=0;
 505            out_dflt="1";
 506        } break;
 507        case algo_lib_FieldId_sig: { // dmmeta.fflag: emptyval specified; no argument required but value may be specified as d:value
 508            *out_anon = false;
 509            retval=0;
 510            out_dflt="Y";
 511        } break;
 512        case algo_lib_FieldId_h: { // bool: no argument required but value may be specified as sig:Y
 513            *out_anon = false;
 514            retval=0;
 515            out_dflt="Y";
 516        } break;
 517        default:
 518        retval=-1; // unrecognized
 519    }
 520    return retval;
 521}

 523// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.Addary
 524// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
 525// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
 526// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
 527algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> algo_lib::ary_tok_Addary(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse, algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> rhs) {
 528    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= csvparse.ary_tok_elems && rhs.elems < csvparse.ary_tok_elems + csvparse.ary_tok_max;
 529    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
 530        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_alias  field:algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
 531    }
 532    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
 533    ary_tok_Reserve(csvparse, nnew); // reserve space
 534    int at = csvparse.ary_tok_n;
 535    for (int i = 0; i < nnew; i++) {
 536        new (csvparse.ary_tok_elems + at + i) algo::cstring(rhs[i]);
 537        csvparse.ary_tok_n++;
 538    }
 539    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(csvparse.ary_tok_elems + at, nnew);
 540}
 541
 542// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.Alloc
 543// Reserve space. Insert element at the end
 544// The new element is initialized to a default value
 545algo::cstring& algo_lib::ary_tok_Alloc(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse) {
 546    ary_tok_Reserve(csvparse, 1);
 547    int n  = csvparse.ary_tok_n;
 548    int at = n;
 549    algo::cstring *elems = csvparse.ary_tok_elems;
 550    new (elems + at) algo::cstring(); // construct new element, default initializer
 551    csvparse.ary_tok_n = n+1;
 552    return elems[at];
 553}
 554
 555// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.AllocAt
 556// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
 557// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
 558algo::cstring& algo_lib::ary_tok_AllocAt(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse, int at) {
 559    ary_tok_Reserve(csvparse, 1);
 560    int n  = csvparse.ary_tok_n;
 561    if (UNLIKELY(u64(at) >= u64(n+1))) {
 562        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.bad_alloc_at  field:algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok  comment:'index out of range'");
 563    }
 564    algo::cstring *elems = csvparse.ary_tok_elems;
 565    memmove(elems + at + 1, elems + at, (n - at) * sizeof(algo::cstring));
 566    new (elems + at) algo::cstring(); // construct element, default initializer
 567    csvparse.ary_tok_n = n+1;
 568    return elems[at];
 569}
 570
 571// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.AllocN
 572// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
 573algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> algo_lib::ary_tok_AllocN(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse, int n_elems) {
 574    ary_tok_Reserve(csvparse, n_elems);
 575    int old_n  = csvparse.ary_tok_n;
 576    int new_n = old_n + n_elems;
 577    algo::cstring *elems = csvparse.ary_tok_elems;
 578    for (int i = old_n; i < new_n; i++) {
 579        new (elems + i) algo::cstring(); // construct new element, default initialize
 580    }
 581    csvparse.ary_tok_n = new_n;
 582    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(elems + old_n, n_elems);
 583}
 584
 585// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.Remove
 586// Remove item by index. If index outside of range, do nothing.
 587void algo_lib::ary_tok_Remove(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse, u32 i) {
 588    u32 lim = csvparse.ary_tok_n;
 589    algo::cstring *elems = csvparse.ary_tok_elems;
 590    if (i < lim) {
 591        elems[i].~cstring(); // destroy element
 592        memmove(elems + i, elems + (i + 1), sizeof(algo::cstring) * (lim - (i + 1)));
 593        csvparse.ary_tok_n = lim - 1;
 594    }
 595}
 596
 597// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.RemoveAll
 598void algo_lib::ary_tok_RemoveAll(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse) {
 599    u32 n = csvparse.ary_tok_n;
 600    while (n > 0) {
 601        n -= 1;
 602        csvparse.ary_tok_elems[n].~cstring();
 603        csvparse.ary_tok_n = n;
 604    }
 605}
 606
 607// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.RemoveLast
 608// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 609void algo_lib::ary_tok_RemoveLast(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse) {
 610    u64 n = csvparse.ary_tok_n;
 611    if (n > 0) {
 612        n -= 1;
 613        ary_tok_qFind(csvparse, u64(n)).~cstring();
 614        csvparse.ary_tok_n = n;
 615    }
 616}
 617
 618// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.AbsReserve
 619// Make sure N elements fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
 620void algo_lib::ary_tok_AbsReserve(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse, int n) {
 621    u32 old_max  = csvparse.ary_tok_max;
 622    if (n > i32(old_max)) {
 623        u32 new_max  = i32_Max(i32_Max(old_max * 2, n), 4);
 624        void *new_mem = algo_lib::lpool_ReallocMem(csvparse.ary_tok_elems, old_max * sizeof(algo::cstring), new_max * sizeof(algo::cstring));
 625        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 626            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_nomem  field:algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok  comment:'out of memory'");
 627        }
 628        csvparse.ary_tok_elems = (algo::cstring*)new_mem;
 629        csvparse.ary_tok_max = new_max;
 630    }
 631}

 633// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.Setary
 634// Copy contents of RHS to PARENT.
 635void algo_lib::ary_tok_Setary(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse, algo_lib::CsvParse &rhs) {
 636    ary_tok_RemoveAll(csvparse);
 637    int nnew = rhs.ary_tok_n;
 638    ary_tok_Reserve(csvparse, nnew); // reserve space
 639    for (int i = 0; i < nnew; i++) { // copy elements over
 640        new (csvparse.ary_tok_elems + i) algo::cstring(ary_tok_qFind(rhs, i));
 641        csvparse.ary_tok_n = i + 1;
 642    }
 643}

 645// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.Setary2
 646// Copy specified array into ary_tok, discarding previous contents.
 647// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), throw exception.
 648void algo_lib::ary_tok_Setary(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse, const algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> &rhs) {
 649    ary_tok_RemoveAll(csvparse);
 650    ary_tok_Addary(csvparse, rhs);
 651}

 653// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.AllocNVal
 654// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
 655algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> algo_lib::ary_tok_AllocNVal(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse, int n_elems, const algo::cstring& val) {
 656    ary_tok_Reserve(csvparse, n_elems);
 657    int old_n  = csvparse.ary_tok_n;
 658    int new_n = old_n + n_elems;
 659    algo::cstring *elems = csvparse.ary_tok_elems;
 660    for (int i = old_n; i < new_n; i++) {
 661        new (elems + i) algo::cstring(val);
 662    }
 663    csvparse.ary_tok_n = new_n;
 664    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(elems + old_n, n_elems);
 665}

 667// --- algo_lib.CsvParse.ary_tok.ReadStrptrMaybe
 668// A single element is read from input string and appended to the array.
 669// If the string contains an error, the array is untouched.
 670// Function returns success value.
 671bool algo_lib::ary_tok_ReadStrptrMaybe(algo_lib::CsvParse& csvparse, algo::strptr in_str) {
 672    bool retval = true;
 673    algo::cstring &elem = ary_tok_Alloc(csvparse);
 674    retval = algo::cstring_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, in_str);
 675    if (!retval) {
 676        ary_tok_RemoveLast(csvparse);
 677    }
 678    return retval;
 679}

 743bool algo_lib::FTimehook_ReadFieldMaybe(algo_lib::FTimehook& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 744    bool retval = true;
 745    algo_lib::FieldId field_id;
 746    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 747    switch(field_id) {
 748        case algo_lib_FieldId_time: {
 749            retval = algo::SchedTime_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.time, strval);
 750            break;
 751        }
 752        case algo_lib_FieldId_delay: {
 753            retval = algo::SchedTime_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.delay, strval);
 754            break;
 755        }
 756        case algo_lib_FieldId_hook: {
 757            retval = false;
 758            break;
 759        }
 760        case algo_lib_FieldId_recurrent: {
 761            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.recurrent, strval);
 762            break;
 763        }
 764        default: break;
 765    }
 766    if (!retval) {
 767        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 768    }
 769    return retval;
 770}

 916// --- algo_lib.FDb.sbrk.AllocMem
 917// Allocate a new piece of memory at least SIZE bytes long.
 918// If out of memory, return NULL
 919// Newly allocated memory is initialized to zeros
 920void* algo_lib::sbrk_AllocMem(u32 size) {
 921    void *ret;
 922#if defined(__MACH__) || __FreeBSD__>0 || __CYGWIN__>0 || defined(WIN32)
 923    ret = malloc(size);
 924#else
 925    ret = MAP_FAILED;
 926    u32 bigsize = 1024*2048;
 927    if (size >= bigsize) { // big block -- will be registered
 928        size = (size + bigsize - 1) / bigsize * bigsize;
 929        int prot = PROT_READ | PROT_WRITE;
 930        int flags = MAP_PRIVATE | MAP_ANONYMOUS | MAP_POPULATE;
 931        bool use_huge = _db.sbrk_huge_alloc + size < _db.sbrk_huge_limit;
 932        if (use_huge) {
 933            ret = mmap(0x0, size, prot, flags | MAP_HUGETLB, 0, 0); // try huge pages
 934        }
 935        // linux huge page handling is buggy -- MAP_POPULATE doesn't guarantee
 936        // that pages are there. subsequent page fault may cause a SIGBUS.
 937        // fortunately there is a way to detect this condition using mlock.
 938        if (use_huge && ret != MAP_FAILED) {
 939            int rc = mlock(ret, size);
 940            if (rc!=0) {
 941                munmap(ret,size);
 942                ret=MAP_FAILED;
 943            } else {
 944                _db.sbrk_huge_alloc += size;
 945            }
 946        }
 947        if (ret == MAP_FAILED) { // try regular mmap
 948            _db.sbrk_huge_limit = 0; // don't try huge pages again
 949            ret = mmap(0x0, size, prot, flags, 0, 0);
 950        } else {
 951            ++algo_lib::_db.trace.n_mmap; // mmap counter
 952        }
 953    } else {
 954        if (ret == MAP_FAILED) { // default method
 955            ret = sbrk(size);
 956            ++algo_lib::_db.trace.n_sbrk; // update global counter
 957        }
 958    }
 959    if (ret == (void*)-1) { // sbrk returns -1 on error
 960        ret = NULL;
 961    }
 962#endif
 963    if (ret && _db.sbrk_zeromem) {
 964        memset(ret,0,size); // touch all bytes in the new memory block
 965    }
 966    return ret;
 967}
 968
 969// --- algo_lib.FDb.sbrk.FreeMem
 970void algo_lib::sbrk_FreeMem(void *mem, u32 size) {
 971#if defined(__MACH__) || __FreeBSD__>0 || defined(WIN32)
 972    free(mem);
 973    (void)size;
 974#else
 975    u32 bigsize = 1024*2048;
 976    if (size >= bigsize) {
 977        munmap((void*)mem, size);
 978    }
 979#endif
 980}

 982// --- algo_lib.FDb.lpool.FreeMem
 983// Free block of memory previously returned by Lpool.
 984void algo_lib::lpool_FreeMem(void* mem, u64 size) {
 985    size = u64_Max(size,1ULL<<4);
 986    u64 cell = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(size-1) + 1 - 4;
 987    if (mem && cell < 36) {
 988        lpool_Lpblock *temp = (lpool_Lpblock*)mem; // push  singly linked list
 989        temp->next = _db.lpool_free[cell];
 990        _db.lpool_free[cell] = temp;
 991    }
 992}
 993
 994// --- algo_lib.FDb.lpool.AllocMem
 995// Allocate new piece of memory at least SIZE bytes long.
 996// If not successful, return NULL
 997// The allocated block is at least 1<<4
 998// The maximum allocation size is at most 1<<(36+4)
 999void* algo_lib::lpool_AllocMem(u64 size) {
1000    void *retval = NULL;
1001    size     = u64_Max(size,1<<4); // enforce alignment
1002    u64 cell = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(size-1) + 1 - 4;
1003    if (cell < 36) {
1004        u64 i    = cell;
1005        // try to find a block that's at least as large as required.
1006        // if found, remove from free list
1007        for (; i < 36; i++) {
1008            lpool_Lpblock *blk = _db.lpool_free[i];
1009            if (blk) {
1010                _db.lpool_free[i] = blk->next;
1011                retval = blk;
1012                break;
1013            }
1014        }
1015        // if suitable size block is not found, create a new one
1016        // by requesting a block from the base allocator.
1017        if (UNLIKELY(!retval)) {
1018            i = u64_Max(cell, 21-4); // 2MB min -- allow huge page to be used
1019            retval = algo_lib::sbrk_AllocMem(1ULL<<(i+4));
1020        }
1021        if (LIKELY(retval)) {
1022            // if block is more than 2x as large as needed, return the upper half to the free
1023            // list (repeatedly). meanwhile, retval doesn't change.
1024            while (i > cell) {
1025                i--;
1026                int half = 1ULL<<(i+4);
1027                lpool_Lpblock *blk = (lpool_Lpblock*)((u8*)retval + half);
1028                blk->next = _db.lpool_free[i];
1029                _db.lpool_free[i] = blk;
1030            }
1031        }
1032    }
1033    return retval;
1034}
1035
1036// --- algo_lib.FDb.lpool.ReserveBuffers
1037// Add N buffers of some size to the free store
1038// Reserve NBUF buffers of size BUFSIZE from the base pool (algo_lib::sbrk)
1039bool algo_lib::lpool_ReserveBuffers(u64 nbuf, u64 bufsize) {
1040    bool retval = true;
1041    bufsize = u64_Max(bufsize, 1<<4);
1042    u64 cell = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(bufsize-1) + 1 - 4;
1043    if (cell < 36) {
1044        for (u64 i = 0; i < nbuf; i++) {
1045            u64 size = 1ULL<<(cell+4);
1046            lpool_Lpblock *temp = (lpool_Lpblock*)algo_lib::sbrk_AllocMem(size);
1047            if (temp == NULL) {
1048                retval = false;
1049                break;// why continue?
1050            } else {
1051                temp->next = _db.lpool_free[cell];
1052                _db.lpool_free[cell] = temp;
1053            }
1054        }
1055    }
1056    return retval;
1057}
1058
1059// --- algo_lib.FDb.lpool.ReallocMem
1060// Allocate new block, copy old to new, delete old.
1061// If the new size is same as old size, do nothing.
1062// In all other cases, new memory is allocated (i.e. size reduction is not a no-op)
1063// If no memory, return NULL; old memory remains untouched
1064void* algo_lib::lpool_ReallocMem(void* oldmem, u64 old_size, u64 new_size) {
1065    void *ret = oldmem;
1066    if (new_size != old_size) {
1067        ret = lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
1068        if (ret && oldmem) {
1069            memcpy(ret,oldmem,u64_Min(new_size,old_size));
1070            lpool_FreeMem(oldmem, old_size);
1071        }
1072    }
1073    return ret;
1074}

1287// Create new row from struct.
1288// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)

1300// --- algo_lib.FDb.imtable.AllocMem
1301// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
1302void* algo_lib::imtable_AllocMem() {
1303    u64 new_nelems     = _db.imtable_n+1;
1304    // compute level and index on level
1305    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
1306    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
1307    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
1308    void *ret = NULL;
1309    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
1310    algo_lib::FImtable*  lev   = NULL;
1311    if (bsr < 32) {
1312        lev = _db.imtable_lary[bsr];
1313        if (!lev) {
1314            lev=(algo_lib::FImtable*)algo_lib::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(algo_lib::FImtable) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
1315            _db.imtable_lary[bsr] = lev;
1316        }
1317    }
1318    // allocate element from this level
1319    if (lev) {
1320        _db.imtable_n = i32(new_nelems);
1321        ret = lev + index;
1322    }
1323    return ret;
1324}
1325
1326// --- algo_lib.FDb.imtable.RemoveAll
1327// Remove all elements from Lary
1328void algo_lib::imtable_RemoveAll() {
1329    for (u64 n = _db.imtable_n; n>0; ) {
1330        n--;
1331        imtable_qFind(u64(n)).~FImtable(); // destroy last element
1332        _db.imtable_n = i32(n);
1333    }
1334}
1335
1336// --- algo_lib.FDb.imtable.RemoveLast
1337// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
1338void algo_lib::imtable_RemoveLast() {
1339    u64 n = _db.imtable_n;
1340    if (n > 0) {
1341        n -= 1;
1342        imtable_qFind(u64(n)).~FImtable();
1343        _db.imtable_n = i32(n);
1344    }
1345}

1347// --- algo_lib.FDb.imtable.XrefMaybe
1348// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1349// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1350bool algo_lib::imtable_XrefMaybe(algo_lib::FImtable &row) {
1351    bool retval = true;
1352    (void)row;

1354    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition

1359            return false;

1365// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_imtable.Find
1366// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
1367algo_lib::FImtable* algo_lib::ind_imtable_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
1368    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_imtable_buckets_n - 1);
1369    algo_lib::FImtable* *e = &_db.ind_imtable_buckets_elems[index];
1370    algo_lib::FImtable* ret=NULL;
1371    do {
1372        ret       = *e;
1373        bool done = !ret || (*ret).imtable == key;
1374        if (done) break;
1375        e         = &ret->ind_imtable_next;
1376    } while (true);
1377    return ret;
1378}

1380// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_imtable.GetOrCreate
1381// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
1382algo_lib::FImtable& algo_lib::ind_imtable_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
1383    algo_lib::FImtable* ret = ind_imtable_Find(key);
1384    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
1385        ret         = &imtable_Alloc();
1386        (*ret).imtable = key;
1387        bool good = imtable_XrefMaybe(*ret);
1388        if (!good) {
1389            imtable_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1390            ret = NULL;
1391        }
1392    }
1393    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "algo_lib.create_error  table:ind_imtable  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
1394    return *ret;
1395}

1397// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_imtable.InsertMaybe
1398// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
1399bool algo_lib::ind_imtable_InsertMaybe(algo_lib::FImtable& row) {
1400    ind_imtable_Reserve(1);
1401    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
1402    if (LIKELY(row.ind_imtable_next == (algo_lib::FImtable*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1403        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.imtable) & (_db.ind_imtable_buckets_n - 1);
1404        algo_lib::FImtable* *prev = &_db.ind_imtable_buckets_elems[index];
1405        do {
1406            algo_lib::FImtable* ret = *prev;
1407            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
1408                break;
1409            }
1410            if ((*ret).imtable == row.imtable) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
1411                retval = false;
1412                break;
1413            }
1414            prev = &ret->ind_imtable_next;
1415        } while (true);
1416        if (retval) {
1417            row.ind_imtable_next = *prev;
1418            _db.ind_imtable_n++;
1419            *prev = &row;
1420        }
1421    }
1422    return retval;
1423}
1424
1425// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_imtable.Remove
1426// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
1427void algo_lib::ind_imtable_Remove(algo_lib::FImtable& row) {
1428    if (LIKELY(row.ind_imtable_next != (algo_lib::FImtable*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1429        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.imtable) & (_db.ind_imtable_buckets_n - 1);
1430        algo_lib::FImtable* *prev = &_db.ind_imtable_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
1431        while (algo_lib::FImtable *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
1432            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
1433                *prev = next->ind_imtable_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
1434                _db.ind_imtable_n--;
1435                row.ind_imtable_next = (algo_lib::FImtable*)-1;// not-in-hash
1436                break;
1437            }
1438            prev = &next->ind_imtable_next;
1439        }
1440    }
1441}
1442
1443// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_imtable.Reserve
1444// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
1445void algo_lib::ind_imtable_Reserve(int n) {
1446    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_imtable_buckets_n;
1447    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_imtable_n + n;
1448    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
1449    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
1450        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
1451        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(algo_lib::FImtable*);
1452        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(algo_lib::FImtable*);
1453        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
1454        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
1455        algo_lib::FImtable* *new_buckets = (algo_lib::FImtable**)algo_lib::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
1456        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
1457            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.out_of_memory  field:algo_lib.FDb.ind_imtable");
1458        }
1459        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
1460        // rehash all entries
1461        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_imtable_buckets_n; i++) {
1462            algo_lib::FImtable* elem = _db.ind_imtable_buckets_elems[i];
1463            while (elem) {
1464                algo_lib::FImtable &row        = *elem;
1465                algo_lib::FImtable* next       = row.ind_imtable_next;
1466                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.imtable) & (new_nbuckets-1);
1467                row.ind_imtable_next     = new_buckets[index];
1468                new_buckets[index] = &row;
1469                elem               = next;
1470            }
1471        }
1472        // free old array
1473        algo_lib::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_imtable_buckets_elems, old_size);
1474        _db.ind_imtable_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
1475        _db.ind_imtable_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
1476    }
1477}

1609// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.Dealloc
1610// Remove all elements from heap and free memory used by the array.
1611void algo_lib::bh_timehook_Dealloc() {
1612    bh_timehook_RemoveAll();
1613    algo_lib::lpool_FreeMem(_db.bh_timehook_elems, sizeof(algo_lib::FTimehook*)*_db.bh_timehook_max);
1614    _db.bh_timehook_max   = 0;
1615    _db.bh_timehook_elems = NULL;
1616}
1617
1618// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.Downheap
1619// Find new location for ROW starting at IDX
1620// NOTE: Rest of heap is rearranged, but pointer to ROW is NOT stored in array.
1621static int algo_lib::bh_timehook_Downheap(algo_lib::FTimehook& row, int idx) {
1622    algo_lib::FTimehook* *elems = _db.bh_timehook_elems;
1623    int n = _db.bh_timehook_n;
1624    int child = idx*2+1;
1625    while (child < n) {
1626        algo_lib::FTimehook* p = elems[child]; // left child
1627        int rchild = child+1;
1628        if (rchild < n) {
1629            algo_lib::FTimehook* q = elems[rchild]; // right child
1630            if (bh_timehook_ElemLt(*q,*p)) {
1631                child = rchild;
1632                p     = q;
1633            }
1634        }
1635        if (!bh_timehook_ElemLt(*p,row)) {
1636            break;
1637        }
1638        p->bh_timehook_idx   = idx;
1639        elems[idx]     = p;
1640        idx            = child;
1641        child          = idx*2+1;
1642    }
1643    return idx;
1644}
1645
1646// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.Insert
1647// Insert row. Row must not already be in index. If row is already in index, do nothing.
1648void algo_lib::bh_timehook_Insert(algo_lib::FTimehook& row) {
1649    if (LIKELY(row.bh_timehook_idx == -1)) {
1650        bh_timehook_Reserve(1);
1651        int n = _db.bh_timehook_n;
1652        _db.bh_timehook_n = n + 1;
1653        int new_idx = bh_timehook_Upheap(row, n);
1654        row.bh_timehook_idx = new_idx;
1655        _db.bh_timehook_elems[new_idx] = &row;
1656        if (new_idx==0) {
1657            bh_timehook_FirstChanged();
1658        }
1659    }
1660}
1661
1662// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.Reheap
1663// If row is in heap, update its position. If row is not in heap, insert it.
1664// Return new position of item in the heap (0=top)
1665// If first item of the is changed, update fstep:algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook
1666i32 algo_lib::bh_timehook_Reheap(algo_lib::FTimehook& row) {
1667    int old_idx = row.bh_timehook_idx;
1668    bool isnew = old_idx == -1;
1669    if (isnew) {
1670        bh_timehook_Reserve(1);
1671        old_idx = _db.bh_timehook_n++;
1672    }
1673    int new_idx = bh_timehook_Upheap(row, old_idx);
1674    if (!isnew && new_idx == old_idx) {
1675        new_idx = bh_timehook_Downheap(row, old_idx);
1676    }
1677    row.bh_timehook_idx = new_idx;
1678    _db.bh_timehook_elems[new_idx] = &row;
1679    bool changed = new_idx==0 || old_idx==0;
1680    if (changed) {
1681        bh_timehook_FirstChanged();
1682    }
1683    return new_idx;
1684}
1685
1686// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.ReheapFirst
1687// Key of first element in the heap changed. Move it.
1688// This function does not check the insert condition.
1689// Return new position of item in the heap (0=top).
1690// Heap must be non-empty or behavior is undefined.
1691// Update fstep:algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook
1692i32 algo_lib::bh_timehook_ReheapFirst() {
1693    algo_lib::FTimehook &row = *_db.bh_timehook_elems[0];
1694    i32 new_idx = bh_timehook_Downheap(row, 0);
1695    row.bh_timehook_idx = new_idx;
1696    _db.bh_timehook_elems[new_idx] = &row;
1697    if (new_idx != 0) {
1698        bh_timehook_FirstChanged();
1699    }
1700    return new_idx;
1701}
1702
1703// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.Remove
1704// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
1705void algo_lib::bh_timehook_Remove(algo_lib::FTimehook& row) {
1706    if (bh_timehook_InBheapQ(row)) {
1707        int old_idx = row.bh_timehook_idx;
1708        if (_db.bh_timehook_elems[old_idx] == &row) { // sanity check: heap points back to row
1709            row.bh_timehook_idx = -1;           // mark not in heap
1710            i32 n = _db.bh_timehook_n - 1; // index of last element in heap
1711            _db.bh_timehook_n = n;         // decrease count
1712            if (old_idx != n) {
1713                algo_lib::FTimehook *elem = _db.bh_timehook_elems[n];
1714                int new_idx = bh_timehook_Upheap(*elem, old_idx);
1715                if (new_idx == old_idx) {
1716                    new_idx = bh_timehook_Downheap(*elem, old_idx);
1717                }
1718                elem->bh_timehook_idx = new_idx;
1719                _db.bh_timehook_elems[new_idx] = elem;
1720            }
1721            if (old_idx == 0) {
1722                bh_timehook_FirstChanged();
1723            }
1724        }
1725    }
1726}
1727
1728// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.RemoveAll
1729// Remove all elements from binary heap
1730void algo_lib::bh_timehook_RemoveAll() {
1731    int n = _db.bh_timehook_n;
1732    for (int i = n - 1; i>=0; i--) {
1733        _db.bh_timehook_elems[i]->bh_timehook_idx = -1; // mark not-in-heap
1734    }
1735    _db.bh_timehook_n = 0;
1736    if (n > 0) {
1737        bh_timehook_FirstChanged();
1738    }
1739}
1740
1741// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.RemoveFirst
1742// If index is empty, return NULL. Otherwise remove and return first key in index.
1743//  Call 'head changed' trigger.
1744algo_lib::FTimehook* algo_lib::bh_timehook_RemoveFirst() {
1745    algo_lib::FTimehook *row = NULL;
1746    if (_db.bh_timehook_n > 0) {
1747        row = _db.bh_timehook_elems[0];
1748        row->bh_timehook_idx = -1;           // mark not in heap
1749        i32 n = _db.bh_timehook_n - 1; // index of last element in heap
1750        _db.bh_timehook_n = n;         // decrease count
1751        if (n) {
1752            algo_lib::FTimehook &elem = *_db.bh_timehook_elems[n];
1753            int new_idx = bh_timehook_Downheap(elem, 0);
1754            elem.bh_timehook_idx = new_idx;
1755            _db.bh_timehook_elems[new_idx] = &elem;
1756        }
1757        bh_timehook_FirstChanged();
1758    }
1759    return row;
1760}
1761
1762// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.Reserve
1763// Reserve space in index for N more elements
1764void algo_lib::bh_timehook_Reserve(int n) {
1765    i32 old_max = _db.bh_timehook_max;
1766    if (UNLIKELY(_db.bh_timehook_n + n > old_max)) {
1767        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
1768        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(algo_lib::FTimehook*);
1769        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(algo_lib::FTimehook*);
1770        void *new_mem = algo_lib::lpool_ReallocMem(_db.bh_timehook_elems, old_size, new_size);
1771        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
1772            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.out_of_memory  field:algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook");
1773        }
1774        _db.bh_timehook_elems = (algo_lib::FTimehook**)new_mem;
1775        _db.bh_timehook_max = new_max;
1776    }
1777}
1778
1779// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.Upheap
1780// Find and return index of new location for element ROW in the heap, starting at index IDX.
1781// Move any elements along the way but do not modify ROW.
1782static int algo_lib::bh_timehook_Upheap(algo_lib::FTimehook& row, int idx) {
1783    algo_lib::FTimehook* *elems = _db.bh_timehook_elems;
1784    while (idx>0) {
1785        int j = (idx-1)/2;
1786        algo_lib::FTimehook* p = elems[j];
1787        if (!bh_timehook_ElemLt(row, *p)) {
1788            break;
1789        }
1790        p->bh_timehook_idx = idx;
1791        elems[idx] = p;
1792        idx = j;
1793    }
1794    return idx;
1795}

1797// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.ElemLt
1798inline static bool algo_lib::bh_timehook_ElemLt(algo_lib::FTimehook &a, algo_lib::FTimehook &b) {
1799    (void)_db;
1800    return time_Lt(a, b);
1801}

1806}

1808// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook.UpdateCycles
1809// Update cycles count from previous clock capture
1810void algo_lib::bh_timehook_UpdateCycles() {
1811    u64 cur_cycles                      = algo::get_cycles();
1812    u64 prev_cycles                     = algo_lib::_db.clock.value;
1813    ++algo_lib::_db.trace.step_bh_timehook;
1814    algo_lib::_db.trace.step_bh_timehook_cycles  += cur_cycles - prev_cycles;
1815    algo_lib::_db.clock                 = algo::SchedTime(cur_cycles);
1816}

1839// --- algo_lib.FDb.dispsigcheck.InsertMaybe
1840// Create new row from struct.
1841// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
1842algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* algo_lib::dispsigcheck_InsertMaybe(const dmmeta::Dispsigcheck &value) {
1843    algo_lib::FDispsigcheck *row = &dispsigcheck_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
1844    dispsigcheck_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dmmeta::Dispsigcheck&>(value));
1845    bool ok = dispsigcheck_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
1846    if (!ok) {
1847        dispsigcheck_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1848        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
1849    }
1850    return row;
1851}

1853// --- algo_lib.FDb.dispsigcheck.AllocMem
1854// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
1855void* algo_lib::dispsigcheck_AllocMem() {
1856    u64 new_nelems     = _db.dispsigcheck_n+1;
1857    // compute level and index on level
1858    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
1859    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
1860    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
1861    void *ret = NULL;
1862    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
1863    algo_lib::FDispsigcheck*  lev   = NULL;
1864    if (bsr < 32) {
1865        lev = _db.dispsigcheck_lary[bsr];
1866        if (!lev) {
1867            lev=(algo_lib::FDispsigcheck*)algo_lib::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(algo_lib::FDispsigcheck) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
1868            _db.dispsigcheck_lary[bsr] = lev;
1869        }
1870    }
1871    // allocate element from this level
1872    if (lev) {
1873        _db.dispsigcheck_n = i32(new_nelems);
1874        ret = lev + index;
1875    }
1876    return ret;
1877}
1878
1879// --- algo_lib.FDb.dispsigcheck.RemoveLast
1880// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
1881void algo_lib::dispsigcheck_RemoveLast() {
1882    u64 n = _db.dispsigcheck_n;
1883    if (n > 0) {
1884        n -= 1;
1885        dispsigcheck_qFind(u64(n)).~FDispsigcheck();
1886        _db.dispsigcheck_n = i32(n);
1887    }
1888}

1890// --- algo_lib.FDb.dispsigcheck.XrefMaybe
1891// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1892// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1893bool algo_lib::dispsigcheck_XrefMaybe(algo_lib::FDispsigcheck &row) {
1894    bool retval = true;
1895    (void)row;
1896    // insert dispsigcheck into index ind_dispsigcheck
1897    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1898        bool success = ind_dispsigcheck_InsertMaybe(row);
1899        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
1900            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
1901            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "algo_lib.duplicate_key  xref:algo_lib.FDb.ind_dispsigcheck"; // check for duplicate key
1902            return false;
1903        }
1904    }
1905    return retval;
1906}

1908// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_dispsigcheck.Find
1909// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
1910algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* algo_lib::ind_dispsigcheck_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
1911    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_n - 1);
1912    algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* *e = &_db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_elems[index];
1913    algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* ret=NULL;
1914    do {
1915        ret       = *e;
1916        bool done = !ret || (*ret).dispsig == key;
1917        if (done) break;
1918        e         = &ret->ind_dispsigcheck_next;
1919    } while (true);
1920    return ret;
1921}
1922
1923// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_dispsigcheck.GetOrCreate
1924// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
1925algo_lib::FDispsigcheck& algo_lib::ind_dispsigcheck_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
1926    algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* ret = ind_dispsigcheck_Find(key);
1927    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
1928        ret         = &dispsigcheck_Alloc();
1929        (*ret).dispsig = key;
1930        bool good = dispsigcheck_XrefMaybe(*ret);
1931        if (!good) {
1932            dispsigcheck_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1933            ret = NULL;
1934        }
1935    }
1936    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "algo_lib.create_error  table:ind_dispsigcheck  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
1937    return *ret;
1938}
1939
1940// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_dispsigcheck.InsertMaybe
1941// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
1942bool algo_lib::ind_dispsigcheck_InsertMaybe(algo_lib::FDispsigcheck& row) {
1943    ind_dispsigcheck_Reserve(1);
1944    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
1945    if (LIKELY(row.ind_dispsigcheck_next == (algo_lib::FDispsigcheck*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1946        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.dispsig) & (_db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_n - 1);
1947        algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* *prev = &_db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_elems[index];
1948        do {
1949            algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* ret = *prev;
1950            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
1951                break;
1952            }
1953            if ((*ret).dispsig == row.dispsig) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
1954                retval = false;
1955                break;
1956            }
1957            prev = &ret->ind_dispsigcheck_next;
1958        } while (true);
1959        if (retval) {
1960            row.ind_dispsigcheck_next = *prev;
1961            _db.ind_dispsigcheck_n++;
1962            *prev = &row;
1963        }
1964    }
1965    return retval;
1966}
1967
1968// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_dispsigcheck.Remove
1969// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
1970void algo_lib::ind_dispsigcheck_Remove(algo_lib::FDispsigcheck& row) {
1971    if (LIKELY(row.ind_dispsigcheck_next != (algo_lib::FDispsigcheck*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1972        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.dispsig) & (_db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_n - 1);
1973        algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* *prev = &_db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
1974        while (algo_lib::FDispsigcheck *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
1975            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
1976                *prev = next->ind_dispsigcheck_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
1977                _db.ind_dispsigcheck_n--;
1978                row.ind_dispsigcheck_next = (algo_lib::FDispsigcheck*)-1;// not-in-hash
1979                break;
1980            }
1981            prev = &next->ind_dispsigcheck_next;
1982        }
1983    }
1984}
1985
1986// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_dispsigcheck.Reserve
1987// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
1988void algo_lib::ind_dispsigcheck_Reserve(int n) {
1989    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_n;
1990    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_dispsigcheck_n + n;
1991    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
1992    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
1993        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
1994        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(algo_lib::FDispsigcheck*);
1995        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(algo_lib::FDispsigcheck*);
1996        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
1997        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
1998        algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* *new_buckets = (algo_lib::FDispsigcheck**)algo_lib::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
1999        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
2000            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.out_of_memory  field:algo_lib.FDb.ind_dispsigcheck");
2001        }
2002        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
2003        // rehash all entries
2004        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_n; i++) {
2005            algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* elem = _db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_elems[i];
2006            while (elem) {
2007                algo_lib::FDispsigcheck &row        = *elem;
2008                algo_lib::FDispsigcheck* next       = row.ind_dispsigcheck_next;
2009                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.dispsig) & (new_nbuckets-1);
2010                row.ind_dispsigcheck_next     = new_buckets[index];
2011                new_buckets[index] = &row;
2012                elem               = next;
2013            }
2014        }
2015        // free old array
2016        algo_lib::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_elems, old_size);
2017        _db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
2018        _db.ind_dispsigcheck_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
2019    }
2020}

2043// --- algo_lib.FDb.imdb.InsertMaybe
2044// Create new row from struct.
2045// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)

2047    algo_lib::FImdb *row = &imdb_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
2048    imdb_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<algo::Imdb&>(value));
2049    bool ok = imdb_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
2050    if (!ok) {
2051        imdb_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2052        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
2053    }

2057// --- algo_lib.FDb.imdb.RemoveAll
2058// Destroy all elements of Inlary
2059void algo_lib::imdb_RemoveAll() {
2060    for (u64 n = _db.imdb_n; n>0; ) {
2061        n--;
2062        reinterpret_cast<algo_lib::FImdb*>(_db.imdb_data)[n].~FImdb(); // destroy last element
2063        _db.imdb_n=n;
2064    }
2065}

2068// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
2069void algo_lib::imdb_RemoveLast() {
2070    u64 n = _db.imdb_n;
2071    if (n > 0) {
2072        n -= 1;
2073        reinterpret_cast<algo_lib::FImdb*>(_db.imdb_data)[n].~FImdb();
2074        _db.imdb_n = n;
2075    }
2076}

2087// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_imdb.Find
2088// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
2089algo_lib::FImdb* algo_lib::ind_imdb_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
2090    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_imdb_buckets_n - 1);
2091    algo_lib::FImdb* *e = &_db.ind_imdb_buckets_elems[index];
2092    algo_lib::FImdb* ret=NULL;
2093    do {
2094        ret       = *e;
2095        bool done = !ret || (*ret).imdb == key;
2096        if (done) break;
2097        e         = &ret->ind_imdb_next;
2098    } while (true);
2099    return ret;
2100}

2102// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_imdb.GetOrCreate
2103// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
2104algo_lib::FImdb& algo_lib::ind_imdb_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
2105    algo_lib::FImdb* ret = ind_imdb_Find(key);
2106    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
2107        ret         = &imdb_Alloc();
2108        (*ret).imdb = key;
2109        bool good = imdb_XrefMaybe(*ret);
2110        if (!good) {
2111            imdb_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2112            ret = NULL;
2113        }
2114    }
2115    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "algo_lib.create_error  table:ind_imdb  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
2116    return *ret;
2117}

2119// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_imdb.InsertMaybe
2120// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
2121bool algo_lib::ind_imdb_InsertMaybe(algo_lib::FImdb& row) {
2122    ind_imdb_Reserve(1);
2123    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
2124    if (LIKELY(row.ind_imdb_next == (algo_lib::FImdb*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2125        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.imdb) & (_db.ind_imdb_buckets_n - 1);
2126        algo_lib::FImdb* *prev = &_db.ind_imdb_buckets_elems[index];
2127        do {
2128            algo_lib::FImdb* ret = *prev;
2129            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
2130                break;
2131            }
2132            if ((*ret).imdb == row.imdb) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
2133                retval = false;
2134                break;
2135            }
2136            prev = &ret->ind_imdb_next;
2137        } while (true);
2138        if (retval) {
2139            row.ind_imdb_next = *prev;
2140            _db.ind_imdb_n++;
2141            *prev = &row;
2142        }
2143    }
2144    return retval;
2145}

2147// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_imdb.Remove
2148// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
2149void algo_lib::ind_imdb_Remove(algo_lib::FImdb& row) {
2150    if (LIKELY(row.ind_imdb_next != (algo_lib::FImdb*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2151        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.imdb) & (_db.ind_imdb_buckets_n - 1);
2152        algo_lib::FImdb* *prev = &_db.ind_imdb_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
2153        while (algo_lib::FImdb *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
2154            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
2155                *prev = next->ind_imdb_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
2156                _db.ind_imdb_n--;
2157                row.ind_imdb_next = (algo_lib::FImdb*)-1;// not-in-hash
2158                break;
2159            }
2160            prev = &next->ind_imdb_next;
2161        }
2162    }
2163}

2174        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(algo_lib::FImdb*);

2479// If out of memory, process is killed.
2480algo_lib::FReplvar& algo_lib::replvar_Alloc() {
2481    algo_lib::FReplvar* row = replvar_AllocMaybe();
2482    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
2483        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.out_of_mem  field:algo_lib.FDb.replvar  comment:'Alloc failed'");
2484    }
2485    return *row;
2486}

2489// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
2490algo_lib::FReplvar* algo_lib::replvar_AllocMaybe() {
2491    algo_lib::FReplvar *row = (algo_lib::FReplvar*)replvar_AllocMem();

2498// --- algo_lib.FDb.replvar.Delete
2499// Remove row from all global and cross indices, then deallocate row
2500void algo_lib::replvar_Delete(algo_lib::FReplvar &row) {
2501    row.~FReplvar();
2502    replvar_FreeMem(row);
2503}

2505// --- algo_lib.FDb.replvar.AllocMem
2506// Allocate space for one element
2507// If no memory available, return NULL.
2508void* algo_lib::replvar_AllocMem() {
2509    algo_lib::FReplvar *row = _db.replvar_free;
2510    if (UNLIKELY(!row)) {
2511        replvar_Reserve(1);
2512        row = _db.replvar_free;
2513    }
2514    if (row) {
2515        _db.replvar_free = row->replvar_next;
2516    }
2517    return row;
2518}
2519
2520// --- algo_lib.FDb.replvar.FreeMem
2521// Remove mem from all global and cross indices, then deallocate mem
2522void algo_lib::replvar_FreeMem(algo_lib::FReplvar &row) {
2523    if (UNLIKELY(row.replvar_next != (algo_lib::FReplvar*)-1)) {
2524        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tpool_double_delete  pool:algo_lib.FDb.replvar  comment:'double deletion caught'");
2525    }
2526    row.replvar_next = _db.replvar_free; // insert into free list
2527    _db.replvar_free  = &row;
2528}
2529
2530// --- algo_lib.FDb.replvar.Reserve
2531// Preallocate memory for N more elements
2532// Return number of elements actually reserved.
2533u64 algo_lib::replvar_Reserve(u64 n_elems) {
2534    u64 ret = 0;
2535    while (ret < n_elems) {
2536        u64 size = _db.replvar_blocksize; // underlying allocator is probably Lpool
2537        u64 reserved = replvar_ReserveMem(size);
2538        ret += reserved;
2539        if (reserved == 0) {
2540            break;
2541        }
2542    }
2543    return ret;
2544}
2545
2546// --- algo_lib.FDb.replvar.ReserveMem
2547// Allocate block of given size, break up into small elements and append to free list.
2548// Return number of elements reserved.
2549u64 algo_lib::replvar_ReserveMem(u64 size) {
2550    u64 ret = 0;
2551    if (size >= sizeof(algo_lib::FReplvar)) {
2552        algo_lib::FReplvar *mem = (algo_lib::FReplvar*)algo_lib::lpool_AllocMem(size);
2553        ret = mem ? size / sizeof(algo_lib::FReplvar) : 0;
2554        // add newly allocated elements to the free list;
2555        for (u64 i=0; i < ret; i++) {
2556            mem[i].replvar_next = _db.replvar_free;
2557            _db.replvar_free = mem+i;
2558        }
2559    }
2560    return ret;
2561}

2563// --- algo_lib.FDb.replvar.XrefMaybe
2564// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
2565// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
2566bool algo_lib::replvar_XrefMaybe(algo_lib::FReplvar &row) {
2567    bool retval = true;
2568    (void)row;
2569    algo_lib::Replscope* p_p_replscope = row.p_replscope;
2570    if (UNLIKELY(!p_p_replscope)) {
2571        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "algo_lib.null_ref  xref:algo_lib.Replscope.ind_replvar";
2572        return false;
2573    }
2574    // insert replvar into index ind_replvar
2575    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2576        bool success = ind_replvar_InsertMaybe(*p_p_replscope, row);
2577        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
2578            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
2579            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "algo_lib.duplicate_key  xref:algo_lib.Replscope.ind_replvar"; // check for duplicate key
2580            return false;
2581        }
2582    }
2583    return retval;
2584}

2586// --- algo_lib.FDb.giveup_time.UpdateCycles
2587// Update cycles count from previous clock capture
2588void algo_lib::giveup_time_UpdateCycles() {
2589    u64 cur_cycles                      = algo::get_cycles();
2590    u64 prev_cycles                     = algo_lib::_db.clock.value;
2591    ++algo_lib::_db.trace.step_giveup_time;
2592    algo_lib::_db.trace.step_giveup_time_cycles  += cur_cycles - prev_cycles;
2593    algo_lib::_db.clock                 = algo::SchedTime(cur_cycles);
2594}

2617// --- algo_lib.FDb.logcat.InsertMaybe
2618// Create new row from struct.
2619// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
2620algo_lib::FLogcat* algo_lib::logcat_InsertMaybe(const dmmeta::Logcat &value) {
2621    algo_lib::FLogcat *row = &logcat_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
2622    logcat_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dmmeta::Logcat&>(value));
2623    bool ok = logcat_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
2624    if (!ok) {
2625        logcat_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2626        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
2627    }
2628    return row;
2629}

2631// --- algo_lib.FDb.logcat.RemoveAll
2632// Destroy all elements of Inlary
2633void algo_lib::logcat_RemoveAll() {
2634    for (u64 n = _db.logcat_n; n>0; ) {
2635        n--;
2636        reinterpret_cast<algo_lib::FLogcat*>(_db.logcat_data)[n].~FLogcat(); // destroy last element
2637        _db.logcat_n=n;
2638    }
2639}

2642// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
2643void algo_lib::logcat_RemoveLast() {
2644    u64 n = _db.logcat_n;
2645    if (n > 0) {
2646        n -= 1;
2647        reinterpret_cast<algo_lib::FLogcat*>(_db.logcat_data)[n].~FLogcat();
2648        _db.logcat_n = n;
2649    }
2650}

2691// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_logcat.Find
2692// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
2693algo_lib::FLogcat* algo_lib::ind_logcat_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
2694    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_logcat_buckets_n - 1);
2695    algo_lib::FLogcat* *e = &_db.ind_logcat_buckets_elems[index];
2696    algo_lib::FLogcat* ret=NULL;
2697    do {
2698        ret       = *e;
2699        bool done = !ret || (*ret).logcat == key;
2700        if (done) break;
2701        e         = &ret->ind_logcat_next;
2702    } while (true);
2703    return ret;
2704}

2706// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_logcat.GetOrCreate
2707// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
2708algo_lib::FLogcat& algo_lib::ind_logcat_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
2709    algo_lib::FLogcat* ret = ind_logcat_Find(key);
2710    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
2711        ret         = &logcat_Alloc();
2712        (*ret).logcat = key;
2713        bool good = logcat_XrefMaybe(*ret);
2714        if (!good) {
2715            logcat_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2716            ret = NULL;
2717        }
2718    }
2719    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "algo_lib.create_error  table:ind_logcat  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
2720    return *ret;
2721}

2723// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_logcat.InsertMaybe
2724// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
2725bool algo_lib::ind_logcat_InsertMaybe(algo_lib::FLogcat& row) {
2726    ind_logcat_Reserve(1);
2727    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
2728    if (LIKELY(row.ind_logcat_next == (algo_lib::FLogcat*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2729        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.logcat) & (_db.ind_logcat_buckets_n - 1);
2730        algo_lib::FLogcat* *prev = &_db.ind_logcat_buckets_elems[index];
2731        do {
2732            algo_lib::FLogcat* ret = *prev;
2733            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
2734                break;
2735            }
2736            if ((*ret).logcat == row.logcat) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
2737                retval = false;
2738                break;
2739            }
2740            prev = &ret->ind_logcat_next;
2741        } while (true);
2742        if (retval) {
2743            row.ind_logcat_next = *prev;
2744            _db.ind_logcat_n++;
2745            *prev = &row;
2746        }
2747    }
2748    return retval;
2749}
2750
2751// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_logcat.Remove
2752// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
2753void algo_lib::ind_logcat_Remove(algo_lib::FLogcat& row) {
2754    if (LIKELY(row.ind_logcat_next != (algo_lib::FLogcat*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2755        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.logcat) & (_db.ind_logcat_buckets_n - 1);
2756        algo_lib::FLogcat* *prev = &_db.ind_logcat_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
2757        while (algo_lib::FLogcat *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
2758            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
2759                *prev = next->ind_logcat_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
2760                _db.ind_logcat_n--;
2761                row.ind_logcat_next = (algo_lib::FLogcat*)-1;// not-in-hash
2762                break;
2763            }
2764            prev = &next->ind_logcat_next;
2765        }
2766    }
2767}
2768
2769// --- algo_lib.FDb.ind_logcat.Reserve
2770// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
2771void algo_lib::ind_logcat_Reserve(int n) {
2772    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_logcat_buckets_n;
2773    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_logcat_n + n;
2774    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
2775    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
2776        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
2777        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(algo_lib::FLogcat*);
2778        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(algo_lib::FLogcat*);
2779        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
2780        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
2781        algo_lib::FLogcat* *new_buckets = (algo_lib::FLogcat**)algo_lib::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
2782        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
2783            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.out_of_memory  field:algo_lib.FDb.ind_logcat");
2784        }
2785        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
2786        // rehash all entries
2787        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_logcat_buckets_n; i++) {
2788            algo_lib::FLogcat* elem = _db.ind_logcat_buckets_elems[i];
2789            while (elem) {
2790                algo_lib::FLogcat &row        = *elem;
2791                algo_lib::FLogcat* next       = row.ind_logcat_next;
2792                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.logcat) & (new_nbuckets-1);
2793                row.ind_logcat_next     = new_buckets[index];
2794                new_buckets[index] = &row;
2795                elem               = next;
2796            }
2797        }
2798        // free old array
2799        algo_lib::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_logcat_buckets_elems, old_size);
2800        _db.ind_logcat_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
2801        _db.ind_logcat_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
2802    }
2803}

2805// --- algo_lib.FDb.exec_args.Addary
2806// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
2807// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
2808// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
2809algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> algo_lib::exec_args_Addary(algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> rhs) {
2810    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= _db.exec_args_elems && rhs.elems < _db.exec_args_elems + _db.exec_args_max;
2811    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
2812        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_alias  field:algo_lib.FDb.exec_args  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
2813    }
2814    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
2815    exec_args_Reserve(nnew); // reserve space
2816    int at = _db.exec_args_n;
2817    for (int i = 0; i < nnew; i++) {
2818        new (_db.exec_args_elems + at + i) algo::cstring(rhs[i]);
2819        _db.exec_args_n++;
2820    }
2821    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(_db.exec_args_elems + at, nnew);
2822}

2824// --- algo_lib.FDb.exec_args.Alloc
2825// Reserve space. Insert element at the end
2826// The new element is initialized to a default value
2827algo::cstring& algo_lib::exec_args_Alloc() {
2828    exec_args_Reserve(1);
2829    int n  = _db.exec_args_n;
2830    int at = n;
2831    algo::cstring *elems = _db.exec_args_elems;
2832    new (elems + at) algo::cstring(); // construct new element, default initializer
2833    _db.exec_args_n = n+1;
2834    return elems[at];
2835}

2837// --- algo_lib.FDb.exec_args.AllocAt
2838// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
2839// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
2840algo::cstring& algo_lib::exec_args_AllocAt(int at) {
2841    exec_args_Reserve(1);
2842    int n  = _db.exec_args_n;
2843    if (UNLIKELY(u64(at) >= u64(n+1))) {
2844        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.bad_alloc_at  field:algo_lib.FDb.exec_args  comment:'index out of range'");
2845    }
2846    algo::cstring *elems = _db.exec_args_elems;
2847    memmove(elems + at + 1, elems + at, (n - at) * sizeof(algo::cstring));
2848    new (elems + at) algo::cstring(); // construct element, default initializer
2849    _db.exec_args_n = n+1;
2850    return elems[at];
2851}

2854// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
2855algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> algo_lib::exec_args_AllocN(int n_elems) {

2867// --- algo_lib.FDb.exec_args.Remove
2868// Remove item by index. If index outside of range, do nothing.
2869void algo_lib::exec_args_Remove(u32 i) {
2870    u32 lim = _db.exec_args_n;
2871    algo::cstring *elems = _db.exec_args_elems;
2872    if (i < lim) {
2873        elems[i].~cstring(); // destroy element
2874        memmove(elems + i, elems + (i + 1), sizeof(algo::cstring) * (lim - (i + 1)));
2875        _db.exec_args_n = lim - 1;
2876    }
2877}

2879// --- algo_lib.FDb.exec_args.RemoveAll
2880void algo_lib::exec_args_RemoveAll() {
2881    u32 n = _db.exec_args_n;
2882    while (n > 0) {
2883        n -= 1;
2884        _db.exec_args_elems[n].~cstring();
2885        _db.exec_args_n = n;
2886    }
2887}

2889// --- algo_lib.FDb.exec_args.RemoveLast
2890// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
2891void algo_lib::exec_args_RemoveLast() {
2892    u64 n = _db.exec_args_n;
2893    if (n > 0) {
2894        n -= 1;
2895        exec_args_qFind(u64(n)).~cstring();
2896        _db.exec_args_n = n;
2897    }
2898}

2900// --- algo_lib.FDb.exec_args.AbsReserve
2901// Make sure N elements fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
2902void algo_lib::exec_args_AbsReserve(int n) {
2903    u32 old_max  = _db.exec_args_max;
2904    if (n > i32(old_max)) {
2905        u32 new_max  = i32_Max(i32_Max(old_max * 2, n), 4);
2906        void *new_mem = algo_lib::lpool_ReallocMem(_db.exec_args_elems, old_max * sizeof(algo::cstring), new_max * sizeof(algo::cstring));
2907        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
2908            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_nomem  field:algo_lib.FDb.exec_args  comment:'out of memory'");
2909        }
2910        _db.exec_args_elems = (algo::cstring*)new_mem;
2911        _db.exec_args_max = new_max;
2912    }
2913}

2917algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> algo_lib::exec_args_AllocNVal(int n_elems, const algo::cstring& val) {
2918    exec_args_Reserve(n_elems);

2943// --- algo_lib.FDb.dirstack.Addary
2944// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
2945// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
2946// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
2947algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> algo_lib::dirstack_Addary(algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> rhs) {
2948    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= _db.dirstack_elems && rhs.elems < _db.dirstack_elems + _db.dirstack_max;
2949    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
2950        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_alias  field:algo_lib.FDb.dirstack  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
2951    }
2952    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
2953    dirstack_Reserve(nnew); // reserve space
2954    int at = _db.dirstack_n;
2955    for (int i = 0; i < nnew; i++) {
2956        new (_db.dirstack_elems + at + i) algo::cstring(rhs[i]);
2957        _db.dirstack_n++;
2958    }
2959    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(_db.dirstack_elems + at, nnew);
2960}

2975// --- algo_lib.FDb.dirstack.AllocAt
2976// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
2977// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
2978algo::cstring& algo_lib::dirstack_AllocAt(int at) {
2979    dirstack_Reserve(1);
2980    int n  = _db.dirstack_n;
2981    if (UNLIKELY(u64(at) >= u64(n+1))) {
2982        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.bad_alloc_at  field:algo_lib.FDb.dirstack  comment:'index out of range'");
2983    }
2984    algo::cstring *elems = _db.dirstack_elems;
2985    memmove(elems + at + 1, elems + at, (n - at) * sizeof(algo::cstring));
2986    new (elems + at) algo::cstring(); // construct element, default initializer
2987    _db.dirstack_n = n+1;
2988    return elems[at];

3006// Remove item by index. If index outside of range, do nothing.
3007void algo_lib::dirstack_Remove(u32 i) {
3008    u32 lim = _db.dirstack_n;
3009    algo::cstring *elems = _db.dirstack_elems;
3010    if (i < lim) {
3011        elems[i].~cstring(); // destroy element
3012        memmove(elems + i, elems + (i + 1), sizeof(algo::cstring) * (lim - (i + 1)));
3013        _db.dirstack_n = lim - 1;

3039// Make sure N elements fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
3040void algo_lib::dirstack_AbsReserve(int n) {
3041    u32 old_max  = _db.dirstack_max;
3042    if (n > i32(old_max)) {
3043        u32 new_max  = i32_Max(i32_Max(old_max * 2, n), 4);
3044        void *new_mem = algo_lib::lpool_ReallocMem(_db.dirstack_elems, old_max * sizeof(algo::cstring), new_max * sizeof(algo::cstring));
3045        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
3046            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_nomem  field:algo_lib.FDb.dirstack  comment:'out of memory'");
3047        }
3048        _db.dirstack_elems = (algo::cstring*)new_mem;
3049        _db.dirstack_max = new_max;
3050    }
3051}

3124// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook_curs.Reset
3125// Reset cursor. If HEAP is non-empty, add its top element to CURS.
3126void algo_lib::_db_bh_timehook_curs_Reset(_db_bh_timehook_curs &curs, algo_lib::FDb &parent) {
3127    curs.parent       = &parent;
3128    _db_bh_timehook_curs_Reserve(curs, bh_timehook_N());

3131        algo_lib::FTimehook &first = *parent.bh_timehook_elems[0];

3137// --- algo_lib.FDb.bh_timehook_curs.Next
3138// Advance cursor.
3139void algo_lib::_db_bh_timehook_curs_Next(_db_bh_timehook_curs &curs) {
3140    algo_lib::FTimehook* *elems = curs.temp_elems;
3141    int n = curs.temp_n;
3142    if (n > 0) {
3143        // remove top element from heap
3144        algo_lib::FTimehook* dead = elems[0];
3145        int i       = 0;
3146        algo_lib::FTimehook* last = curs.temp_elems[n-1];
3147        // downheap last elem
3148        do {
3149            algo_lib::FTimehook* choose = last;
3150            int l         = i*2+1;
3151            if (l<n) {
3152                algo_lib::FTimehook* el = elems[l];
3153                int r     = l+1;
3154                r        -= r==n;
3155                algo_lib::FTimehook* er = elems[r];
3156                if (bh_timehook_ElemLt(*er,*el)) {
3157                    el  = er;
3158                    l   = r;
3159                }
3160                bool b = bh_timehook_ElemLt(*el,*last);
3161                if (b) choose = el;
3162                if (!b) l = n;
3163            }
3164            elems[i] = choose;
3165            i = l;
3166        } while (i < n);
3167        curs.temp_n = n-1;
3168        int index = dead->bh_timehook_idx;
3169        i = (index*2+1);
3170        if (i < bh_timehook_N()) {
3171            algo_lib::FTimehook &elem = *curs.parent->bh_timehook_elems[i];
3172            _db_bh_timehook_curs_Add(curs, elem);
3173        }
3174        if (i+1 < bh_timehook_N()) {
3175            algo_lib::FTimehook &elem = *curs.parent->bh_timehook_elems[i + 1];
3176            _db_bh_timehook_curs_Add(curs, elem);
3177        }
3178    }
3179}

3454// --- algo_lib.FTxtrow.sortkey.Nextchar
3455// Extract next character from STR and advance IDX
3456inline static u64 algo_lib::sortkey_Nextchar(const algo_lib::FTxtrow& txtrow, algo::strptr &str, int &idx) {
3457    (void)txtrow;
3458    int i = idx;
3459    u64 ch = str.elems[i];
3460    i++;
3461    // downcase the char for case-insensitive comparison
3462    if (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z') {
3463        ch = ch - 'A' + 'a';
3464    }
3465    // detect number in string and eat it up into CH.
3466    // (this only works for base-10 numbers
3467    // Digits are sorted before chars
3468    if (unsigned(ch - '0') < 10) {
3469        while(i < str.n_elems) { // resulting char sorts before ascii 47
3470            unsigned dig = str.elems[i] - '0';
3471            if (dig >= 10) break;
3472            ch = ch * 10 + dig;
3473            i++;
3474        }
3475    } else if (ch > '9') {
3476        // create space between '0'..'9' for 15-digit numbers
3477        ch += 1000000000000000LL;
3478    }
3479    idx = i;
3480    return ch;
3481}
3482
3483// --- algo_lib.FTxtrow.sortkey.Cmp
3484// Compare two fields.
3485// Comparison uses version sort (detect embedded integers).
3486// Comparison is case-insensitive.
3487i32 algo_lib::sortkey_Cmp(algo_lib::FTxtrow& txtrow, algo_lib::FTxtrow &rhs) {
3488    i32 retval = 0;
3489    int idx_a = 0;
3490    int idx_b = 0;
3491    algo::strptr str_a = ch_Getary(txtrow.sortkey);
3492    algo::strptr str_b = ch_Getary(rhs.sortkey);
3493    int n_a   = elems_N(str_a);
3494    int n_b   = elems_N(str_b);
3495    retval    = i32_Cmp(n_a,n_b);
3496    while (idx_a < n_a && idx_b < n_b) {
3497        u64 ch_a = sortkey_Nextchar(txtrow, str_a, idx_a);
3498        u64 ch_b = sortkey_Nextchar(rhs, str_b, idx_b);
3499        if (ch_a != ch_b) {
3500            retval = (ch_a > ch_b)*2-1;
3501            break;
3502        }
3503    }
3504    return retval;
3505}

3548// --- algo_lib.FTxtrow.c_txtcell.Remove
3549// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
3550void algo_lib::c_txtcell_Remove(algo_lib::FTxtrow& txtrow, algo_lib::FTxtcell& row) {
3551    if (bool_Update(row.txtrow_c_txtcell_in_ary,false)) {
3552        int lim = txtrow.c_txtcell_n;
3553        algo_lib::FTxtcell* *elems = txtrow.c_txtcell_elems;
3554        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
3555        // if found, shift array.
3556        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
3557            algo_lib::FTxtcell* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
3558            if (elem == &row) {
3559                int j = i + 1;
3560                size_t nbytes = sizeof(algo_lib::FTxtcell*) * (lim - j);
3561                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
3562                txtrow.c_txtcell_n = lim - 1;
3563                break;
3564            }
3565        }
3566    }
3567}

3572    u32 old_max = txtrow.c_txtcell_max;
3573    if (UNLIKELY(txtrow.c_txtcell_n + n > old_max)) {
3574        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
3575        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(algo_lib::FTxtcell*);
3576        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(algo_lib::FTxtcell*);
3577        void *new_mem = algo_lib::lpool_ReallocMem(txtrow.c_txtcell_elems, old_size, new_size);
3578        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
3579            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.out_of_memory  field:algo_lib.FTxtrow.c_txtcell");
3580        }
3581        txtrow.c_txtcell_elems = (algo_lib::FTxtcell**)new_mem;
3582        txtrow.c_txtcell_max = new_max;
3583    }
3584}

3695// --- algo_lib.FTxttbl.c_txtrow.Lt
3696// Compare values elem_a and elem_b
3697// The comparison function must be anti-symmetric: if a>b, then !(b>a).
3698// If not, mayhem results.
3699static bool algo_lib::c_txtrow_Lt(algo_lib::FTxtrow &elem_a, algo_lib::FTxtrow &elem_b) {
3700    bool ret;
3701    ret = sortkey_Lt(elem_a, elem_b);
3702    return ret;
3703}

3705// --- algo_lib.FTxttbl.c_txtrow.SortedQ
3706// Verify whether array is sorted
3707bool algo_lib::c_txtrow_SortedQ(algo_lib::FTxttbl& txttbl) {
3708    algo_lib::FTxtrow* *elems = c_txtrow_Getary(txttbl).elems;
3709    int n = c_txtrow_N(txttbl);
3710    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
3711        if (c_txtrow_Lt(*elems[i], *elems[i-1])) {
3712            return false;
3713        }
3714    }
3715    return true;
3716}
