3718// --- algo_lib.FTxttbl.c_txtrow.IntInsertionSort
3719// Internal insertion sort
3720static void algo_lib::c_txtrow_IntInsertionSort(algo_lib::FTxtrow* *elems, int n) {
3721    for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
3722        int j = i;
3723        algo_lib::FTxtrow *tmp = elems[i];
3724        // shift elements up by one
3725        if (c_txtrow_Lt(*tmp, *elems[j-1])) {
3726            do {
3727                elems[j] = elems[j-1];
3728                j--;
3729            } while (j>0 && c_txtrow_Lt(*tmp, *elems[j-1]));
3730            elems[j] = tmp;
3731        }
3732    }
3733}
3734
3735// --- algo_lib.FTxttbl.c_txtrow.IntHeapSort
3736// Internal heap sort
3737static void algo_lib::c_txtrow_IntHeapSort(algo_lib::FTxtrow* *elems, int n) {
3738    // construct max-heap.
3739    // k=current element
3740    // j=parent element
3741    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
3742        int k=i;
3743        int j=(i-1)/2;
3744        while (c_txtrow_Lt(*elems[j], *elems[k])) {
3745            c_txtrow_Swap(elems[k],elems[j]);
3746            k=j;
3747            j=(k-1)/2;
3748        }
3749    }
3750    // remove elements from heap one-by-one,
3751    // deposit them in reverse order starting at the end of ARY.
3752    for (int i = n - 1; i>=0; i--) {
3753        int k = 0;
3754        int l = 1;
3755        while (l<i) {
3756            l += l<i-1 && c_txtrow_Lt(*elems[l], *elems[l+1]);
3757            if (c_txtrow_Lt(*elems[l], *elems[i])) {
3758                break;
3759            }
3760            c_txtrow_Swap(elems[k], elems[l]);
3761            k = l;
3762            l = k*2+1;
3763        }
3764        if (i != k) {
3765            c_txtrow_Swap(elems[i],elems[k]);
3766        }
3767    }
3768}

3770// --- algo_lib.FTxttbl.c_txtrow.IntQuickSort
3771// Quick sort engine
3772static void algo_lib::c_txtrow_IntQuickSort(algo_lib::FTxtrow* *elems, int n, int depth) {
3773    while (n>16) {
3774        // detect degenerate case and revert to heap sort
3775        if (depth==0) {
3776            c_txtrow_IntHeapSort(elems,n);
3777            return;
3778        }
3779        // elements to sort initially to determine pivot.
3780        // choose pp=n/2 in case the input is already sorted.
3781        int pi = 0;
3782        int pp = n/2;
3783        int pj = n-1;
3784        // insertion sort for 1st, middle and last element
3785        if (c_txtrow_Lt(*elems[pp], *elems[pi])) {
3786            c_txtrow_Swap(elems[pi], elems[pp]);
3787        }
3788        if (c_txtrow_Lt(*elems[pj], *elems[pp])) {
3789            if (c_txtrow_Lt(*elems[pj], *elems[pi])) {
3790                c_txtrow_Rotleft(elems[pi], elems[pj], elems[pp]);
3791            } else {
3792                c_txtrow_Swap(elems[pj], elems[pp]);
3793            }
3794        }
3795        // deposit pivot near the end of the array and skip it.
3796        c_txtrow_Swap(elems[--pj], elems[pp]);
3797        // copy pivot into temporary variable
3798        algo_lib::FTxtrow *pivot = elems[pj];
3799        for(;;){
3800            while (c_txtrow_Lt(*elems[++pi], *pivot)) {
3801            }
3802            while (c_txtrow_Lt(*pivot, *elems[--pj])) {
3803            }
3804            if (pj <= pi) {
3805                break;
3806            }
3807            c_txtrow_Swap(elems[pi],elems[pj]);
3808        }
3809        depth -= 1;
3810        c_txtrow_IntQuickSort(elems, pi, depth);
3811        elems += pi;
3812        n -= pi;
3813    }
3814    // sort the remainder of this section
3815    c_txtrow_IntInsertionSort(elems,n);
3816}

3818// --- algo_lib.FTxttbl.c_txtrow.InsertionSort

3820void algo_lib::c_txtrow_InsertionSort(algo_lib::FTxttbl& txttbl) {
3821    algo_lib::FTxtrow* *elems = c_txtrow_Getary(txttbl).elems;
3822    int n = c_txtrow_N(txttbl);
3823    c_txtrow_IntInsertionSort(elems, n);
3824}

3826// --- algo_lib.FTxttbl.c_txtrow.HeapSort
3827// Heap sort
3828void algo_lib::c_txtrow_HeapSort(algo_lib::FTxttbl& txttbl) {
3829    algo_lib::FTxtrow* *elems = c_txtrow_Getary(txttbl).elems;

3834// --- algo_lib.FTxttbl.c_txtrow.QuickSort
3835// Quick sort
3836void algo_lib::c_txtrow_QuickSort(algo_lib::FTxttbl& txttbl) {
3837    // compute max recursion depth based on number of elements in the array
3838    int max_depth = algo::CeilingLog2(u32(c_txtrow_N(txttbl) + 1)) + 3;
3839    algo_lib::FTxtrow* *elems = c_txtrow_Getary(txttbl).elems;
3840    int n = c_txtrow_N(txttbl);
3841    c_txtrow_IntQuickSort(elems, n, max_depth);
3842}

4173// --- algo_lib.Regx.state.AllocAt
4174// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
4175// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
4176algo_lib::RegxState& algo_lib::state_AllocAt(algo_lib::Regx& regx, int at) {
4177    state_Reserve(regx, 1);
4178    int n  = regx.state_n;
4179    if (UNLIKELY(u64(at) >= u64(n+1))) {

4181    }

4183    memmove(elems + at + 1, elems + at, (n - at) * sizeof(algo_lib::RegxState));
4184    new (elems + at) algo_lib::RegxState(); // construct element, default initializer
4185    regx.state_n = n+1;
4186    return elems[at];

4546// --- algo_lib.RegxState.ch_class.Addary
4547// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
4548// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
4549// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
4550algo::aryptr<algo::i32_Range> algo_lib::ch_class_Addary(algo_lib::RegxState& parent, algo::aryptr<algo::i32_Range> rhs) {
4551    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= parent.ch_class_elems && rhs.elems < parent.ch_class_elems + parent.ch_class_max;
4552    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
4553        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_alias  field:algo_lib.RegxState.ch_class  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
4554    }
4555    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
4556    ch_class_Reserve(parent, nnew); // reserve space
4557    int at = parent.ch_class_n;
4558    for (int i = 0; i < nnew; i++) {
4559        new (parent.ch_class_elems + at + i) algo::i32_Range(rhs[i]);
4560        parent.ch_class_n++;
4561    }
4562    return algo::aryptr<algo::i32_Range>(parent.ch_class_elems + at, nnew);
4563}

4678// --- algo_lib.RegxState.ch_class.Swap
4679// Swap values elem_a and elem_b
4680inline static void algo_lib::ch_class_Swap(algo::i32_Range &elem_a, algo::i32_Range &elem_b) {
4681    u8 temp[sizeof(algo::i32_Range)];
4682    memcpy(&temp  , &elem_a, sizeof(algo::i32_Range));
4683    memcpy(&elem_a, &elem_b, sizeof(algo::i32_Range));
4684    memcpy(&elem_b, &temp  , sizeof(algo::i32_Range));
4685}

4687// --- algo_lib.RegxState.ch_class.Rotleft
4688// Left circular shift of three-tuple
4689inline static void algo_lib::ch_class_Rotleft(algo::i32_Range &elem_a, algo::i32_Range &elem_b, algo::i32_Range &elem_c) {
4690    u8 temp[sizeof(algo::i32_Range)];
4691    memcpy(&temp, &elem_a   , sizeof(algo::i32_Range));
4692    memcpy(&elem_a   , &elem_b   , sizeof(algo::i32_Range));
4693    memcpy(&elem_b   , &elem_c   , sizeof(algo::i32_Range));
4694    memcpy(&elem_c   , &temp, sizeof(algo::i32_Range));
4695}

4697// --- algo_lib.RegxState.ch_class.Lt
4698// Compare values elem_a and elem_b
4699// The comparison function must be anti-symmetric: if a>b, then !(b>a).
4700// If not, mayhem results.
4701static bool algo_lib::ch_class_Lt(algo::i32_Range &elem_a, algo::i32_Range &elem_b) {
4702    bool ret;
4703    ret = elem_a.beg < elem_b.beg;
4704    return ret;
4705}

4707// --- algo_lib.RegxState.ch_class.SortedQ
4708// Verify whether array is sorted
4709bool algo_lib::ch_class_SortedQ(algo_lib::RegxState& parent) {
4710    algo::i32_Range *elems = ch_class_Getary(parent).elems;
4711    int n = ch_class_N(parent);
4712    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
4713        if (ch_class_Lt(elems[i], elems[i-1])) {
4714            return false;
4715        }
4716    }
4717    return true;
4718}

4720// --- algo_lib.RegxState.ch_class.IntInsertionSort
4721// Internal insertion sort
4722static void algo_lib::ch_class_IntInsertionSort(algo::i32_Range *elems, int n) {
4723    for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
4724        int j = i;
4725        // find the spot for ith element.
4726        while (j>0 && ch_class_Lt(elems[i], elems[j-1])) {
4727            j--;
4728        }
4729        if (j<i) {
4730            u8 tmp[sizeof(algo::i32_Range)];
4731            memcpy (tmp                       , &elems[i], sizeof(algo::i32_Range)      );
4732            memmove(&elems[j+1], &elems[j], sizeof(algo::i32_Range)*(i-j));
4733            memcpy (&elems[j]  , tmp                     , sizeof(algo::i32_Range)      );
4734        }
4735    }
4736}
4737
4738// --- algo_lib.RegxState.ch_class.IntHeapSort
4739// Internal heap sort
4740static void algo_lib::ch_class_IntHeapSort(algo::i32_Range *elems, int n) {
4741    // construct max-heap.
4742    // k=current element
4743    // j=parent element
4744    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
4745        int k=i;
4746        int j=(i-1)/2;
4747        while (ch_class_Lt(elems[j], elems[k])) {
4748            ch_class_Swap(elems[k],elems[j]);
4749            k=j;
4750            j=(k-1)/2;
4751        }
4752    }
4753    // remove elements from heap one-by-one,
4754    // deposit them in reverse order starting at the end of ARY.
4755    for (int i = n - 1; i>=0; i--) {
4756        int k = 0;
4757        int l = 1;
4758        while (l<i) {
4759            l += l<i-1 && ch_class_Lt(elems[l], elems[l+1]);
4760            if (ch_class_Lt(elems[l], elems[i])) {
4761                break;
4762            }
4763            ch_class_Swap(elems[k], elems[l]);
4764            k = l;
4765            l = k*2+1;
4766        }
4767        if (i != k) {
4768            ch_class_Swap(elems[i],elems[k]);
4769        }
4770    }
4771}
4772
4773// --- algo_lib.RegxState.ch_class.IntQuickSort
4774// Quick sort engine
4775static void algo_lib::ch_class_IntQuickSort(algo::i32_Range *elems, int n, int depth) {
4776    while (n>16) {
4777        // detect degenerate case and revert to heap sort
4778        if (depth==0) {
4779            ch_class_IntHeapSort(elems,n);
4780            return;
4781        }
4782        // elements to sort initially to determine pivot.
4783        // choose pp=n/2 in case the input is already sorted.
4784        int pi = 0;
4785        int pp = n/2;
4786        int pj = n-1;
4787        // insertion sort for 1st, middle and last element
4788        if (ch_class_Lt(elems[pp], elems[pi])) {
4789            ch_class_Swap(elems[pi], elems[pp]);
4790        }
4791        if (ch_class_Lt(elems[pj], elems[pp])) {
4792            if (ch_class_Lt(elems[pj], elems[pi])) {
4793                ch_class_Rotleft(elems[pi], elems[pj], elems[pp]);
4794            } else {
4795                ch_class_Swap(elems[pj], elems[pp]);
4796            }
4797        }
4798        // deposit pivot near the end of the array and skip it.
4799        ch_class_Swap(elems[--pj], elems[pp]);
4800        // reference to pivot
4801        algo::i32_Range &pivot = elems[pj];
4802        for(;;){
4803            while (ch_class_Lt(elems[++pi], pivot)) {
4804            }
4805            while (ch_class_Lt(pivot, elems[--pj])) {
4806            }
4807            if (pj <= pi) {
4808                break;
4809            }
4810            ch_class_Swap(elems[pi],elems[pj]);
4811        }
4812        depth -= 1;
4813        ch_class_IntQuickSort(elems, pi, depth);
4814        elems += pi;
4815        n -= pi;
4816    }
4817    // sort the remainder of this section
4818    ch_class_IntInsertionSort(elems,n);
4819}

4825    int n = ch_class_N(parent);

4858// --- algo_lib.Replscope.ind_replvar.Cascdel
4859// Delete all rows reachable through the hash index
4860void algo_lib::ind_replvar_Cascdel(algo_lib::Replscope& replscope) {
4861    if (replscope.ind_replvar_n) {
4862        for (int i = 0; i < replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_n; i++) {
4863            algo_lib::FReplvar *elem = replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_elems[i];
4864            while (elem) {
4865                algo_lib::FReplvar *next = elem->ind_replvar_next;
4866                replvar_Delete(*elem);
4867                elem = next;
4868            }
4869        }
4870    }
4871}

4873// --- algo_lib.Replscope.ind_replvar.Find
4874// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
4875algo_lib::FReplvar* algo_lib::ind_replvar_Find(algo_lib::Replscope& replscope, const algo::strptr& key) {
4876    u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, key) & (replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_n - 1);
4877    algo_lib::FReplvar* *e = &replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_elems[index];
4878    algo_lib::FReplvar* ret=NULL;
4879    do {
4880        ret       = *e;
4881        bool done = !ret || (*ret).key == key;
4882        if (done) break;
4883        e         = &ret->ind_replvar_next;
4884    } while (true);
4885    return ret;
4886}

4888// --- algo_lib.Replscope.ind_replvar.InsertMaybe
4889// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
4890bool algo_lib::ind_replvar_InsertMaybe(algo_lib::Replscope& replscope, algo_lib::FReplvar& row) {
4891    ind_replvar_Reserve(replscope, 1);
4892    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
4893    if (LIKELY(row.ind_replvar_next == (algo_lib::FReplvar*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
4894        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.key) & (replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_n - 1);
4895        algo_lib::FReplvar* *prev = &replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_elems[index];
4896        do {
4897            algo_lib::FReplvar* ret = *prev;
4898            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
4899                break;
4900            }
4901            if ((*ret).key == row.key) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
4902                retval = false;
4903                break;
4904            }
4905            prev = &ret->ind_replvar_next;
4906        } while (true);
4907        if (retval) {
4908            row.ind_replvar_next = *prev;
4909            replscope.ind_replvar_n++;
4910            *prev = &row;
4911        }
4912    }
4913    return retval;
4914}

4916// --- algo_lib.Replscope.ind_replvar.Remove
4917// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
4918void algo_lib::ind_replvar_Remove(algo_lib::Replscope& replscope, algo_lib::FReplvar& row) {
4919    if (LIKELY(row.ind_replvar_next != (algo_lib::FReplvar*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
4920        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.key) & (replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_n - 1);
4921        algo_lib::FReplvar* *prev = &replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
4922        while (algo_lib::FReplvar *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
4923            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
4924                *prev = next->ind_replvar_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
4925                replscope.ind_replvar_n--;
4926                row.ind_replvar_next = (algo_lib::FReplvar*)-1;// not-in-hash
4927                break;
4928            }
4929            prev = &next->ind_replvar_next;
4930        }
4931    }
4932}
4933
4934// --- algo_lib.Replscope.ind_replvar.Reserve
4935// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
4936void algo_lib::ind_replvar_Reserve(algo_lib::Replscope& replscope, int n) {
4937    u32 old_nbuckets = replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_n;
4938    u32 new_nelems   = replscope.ind_replvar_n + n;
4939    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
4940    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
4941        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
4942        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(algo_lib::FReplvar*);
4943        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(algo_lib::FReplvar*);
4944        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
4945        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
4946        algo_lib::FReplvar* *new_buckets = (algo_lib::FReplvar**)algo_lib::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
4947        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
4948            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.out_of_memory  field:algo_lib.Replscope.ind_replvar");
4949        }
4950        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
4951        // rehash all entries
4952        for (int i = 0; i < replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_n; i++) {
4953            algo_lib::FReplvar* elem = replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_elems[i];
4954            while (elem) {
4955                algo_lib::FReplvar &row        = *elem;
4956                algo_lib::FReplvar* next       = row.ind_replvar_next;
4957                u32 index          = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.key) & (new_nbuckets-1);
4958                row.ind_replvar_next     = new_buckets[index];
4959                new_buckets[index] = &row;
4960                elem               = next;
4961            }
4962        }
4963        // free old array
4964        algo_lib::lpool_FreeMem(replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_elems, old_size);
4965        replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
4966        replscope.ind_replvar_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
4967    }
4968}

4970// --- algo_lib.Replscope.ind_replvar_curs.Reset
4971void algo_lib::replscope_ind_replvar_curs_Reset(replscope_ind_replvar_curs &curs, algo_lib::Replscope &parent) {
4972    curs.bucket = 0;
4973    curs.parent = &parent;
4974    curs.prow = &parent.ind_replvar_buckets_elems[0]; // hash never has zero buckets
4975    while (!*curs.prow) {
4976        curs.bucket += 1;
4977        if (curs.bucket == parent.ind_replvar_buckets_n) break;
4978        curs.prow = &parent.ind_replvar_buckets_elems[curs.bucket];
4979    }
4980}

5102// --- algo_lib.Tabulate.width.Addary
5103// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
5104// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
5105// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
5106algo::aryptr<i32> algo_lib::width_Addary(algo_lib::Tabulate& tabulate, algo::aryptr<i32> rhs) {
5107    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= tabulate.width_elems && rhs.elems < tabulate.width_elems + tabulate.width_max;
5108    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
5109        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_alias  field:algo_lib.Tabulate.width  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
5110    }
5111    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
5112    width_Reserve(tabulate, nnew); // reserve space
5113    int at = tabulate.width_n;
5114    memcpy(tabulate.width_elems + at, rhs.elems, nnew * sizeof(i32));
5115    tabulate.width_n += nnew;
5116    return algo::aryptr<i32>(tabulate.width_elems + at, nnew);
5117}

5119// --- algo_lib.Tabulate.width.Alloc
5120// Reserve space. Insert element at the end
5121// The new element is initialized to a default value
5122i32& algo_lib::width_Alloc(algo_lib::Tabulate& tabulate) {
5123    width_Reserve(tabulate, 1);
5124    int n  = tabulate.width_n;
5125    int at = n;
5126    i32 *elems = tabulate.width_elems;
5127    new (elems + at) i32(0); // construct new element, default initializer
5128    tabulate.width_n = n+1;
5129    return elems[at];
5130}

5132// --- algo_lib.Tabulate.width.AllocAt
5133// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
5134// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
5135i32& algo_lib::width_AllocAt(algo_lib::Tabulate& tabulate, int at) {
5136    width_Reserve(tabulate, 1);
5137    int n  = tabulate.width_n;
5138    if (UNLIKELY(u64(at) >= u64(n+1))) {
5139        FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.bad_alloc_at  field:algo_lib.Tabulate.width  comment:'index out of range'");
5140    }
5141    i32 *elems = tabulate.width_elems;
5142    memmove(elems + at + 1, elems + at, (n - at) * sizeof(i32));
5143    new (elems + at) i32(0); // construct element, default initializer
5144    tabulate.width_n = n+1;
5145    return elems[at];
5146}

5184// Make sure N elements fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
5185void algo_lib::width_AbsReserve(algo_lib::Tabulate& tabulate, int n) {
5186    u32 old_max  = tabulate.width_max;
5187    if (n > i32(old_max)) {
5188        u32 new_max  = i32_Max(i32_Max(old_max * 2, n), 4);
5189        void *new_mem = algo_lib::lpool_ReallocMem(tabulate.width_elems, old_max * sizeof(i32), new_max * sizeof(i32));
5190        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
5191            FatalErrorExit("algo_lib.tary_nomem  field:algo_lib.Tabulate.width  comment:'out of memory'");
5192        }
5193        tabulate.width_elems = (i32*)new_mem;
5194        tabulate.width_max = new_max;
5195    }
5196}
